org.eclipse.gef4.mvc.parts

Interface IRootPart<VR,V extends VR>

  • Type Parameters:
    VR - The visual root node of the UI toolkit used, e.g. javafx.scene.Node in case of JavaFX.
    V - The visual node used by this IRootPart.
    All Superinterfaces:
    IActivatable, IAdaptable, IAdaptable.Bound<IViewer<VR>>, IDisposable, IVisualPart<VR,V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFXRootPart, AbstractRootPart, FXRootPart

    public interface IRootPart<VR,V extends VR>
extends IVisualPart<VR,V>, IAdaptable.Bound<IViewer<VR>>
    A IRootPart is the root controller of an IViewer. It controls the root view and holds IHandlePart and IContentPart children. The IRootPart does not correspond to anything in the model, and typically can not be interacted with by the User. The Root provides a homogeneous context for the applications "real" IVisualPart.
    Noimplement:
    This interface is not intended to be implemented by clients. Instead, AbstractRootPart should be sub-classed.
